    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your surroundings comprise people, lives, &lt;br&gt;
the government, and systems around you, &lt;br&gt;
including family members, office hierarchy, &lt;br&gt;
political setup, religious teachings, elders, youth, &lt;br&gt;
colleagues, even other lives like pets or animals nearby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your relationship with the surroundings is influenced by them. &lt;br&gt;
You aren&amp;rsquo;t entirely responsible for creating a harmonious atmosphere. &lt;br&gt;
Some people are generally good but hostile towards you, &lt;br&gt;
Some are naturally hostile; &lt;br&gt;
If you attempt to change them against their will, &lt;br&gt;
You&amp;rsquo;ll waste your life, time, and energy. &lt;br&gt;
Changing systems, religious beliefs, and &lt;br&gt;
government is an extremely daunting task. &lt;br&gt;
In human history, those who changed their surroundings &lt;br&gt;
didn&amp;rsquo;t do it by changing others, &lt;br&gt;
but by changing themselves.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
